Plot Fit to Catch Data

Source: R/gmacs_plot_catch.R
gmacs_plot_catch.Rd

Plot fits to catch data from Gmacsall.out data summary

gmacs_plot_catch(
  all_out = NULL,
  save_plot = T,
  plot_dir = NULL,
  y_labs = NULL,
  data_summary = NULL,
  file = NULL,
  model_name = NULL,
  version = NULL
)

Arguments

all_out

Output from gmacs_read_allout() as nested list. Example: all_out = list(mod_23.0a, mod_23.1b).

save_plot

T/F save plot. Default = T.

plot_dir

Null. Directory in which to save plot. If NULL, a directory called 'plots' will be created in the same directory as gmacs.dat.

y_labs

NULL. Optional, custom y axis labels as character vector.

data_summary

NULL. Alternate way to bring in data, output of gmacs_get_catch_summary()

file

NULL. File paths to Gmacsall.out for each model to compare, passed to gmacs_read_allout(). Expressed as character vector, not needed if all.out is provided.

model_name

NULL. Character string passed to gmacs_read_allout(). Expressed as character vector, not needed if all.out is provided.

version

NULL. Character string passed to gmacs_read_allout() denoting GMACS version, not needed if all.out is provided.

Value

Plot of fit to catch data by series

Examples

gmacs_plot_catch(all_out = list(model_25.0))
#> Error: object 'model_25.0' not found
